 482:LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c **** /**
 483:LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * @brief This function should be called when a packet is ready to be read
 484:LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * from the interface. It uses the function low_level_input() that
 485:LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * should handle the actual reception of bytes from the network
 486:LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * interface. Then the type of the received packet is determined and
